<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="505" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="21.[741,1333,1188,1616]" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[741,894,1188,1221]" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="d'Orbigny, 1836" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1836" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lophostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="silvicola">Lophostoma silvicola d’Orbigny, 1836</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation latitude="-15.75" longitude="-65.25" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">
“des grandes foréts qui bordent le pied oriental de la Cordillere bolivienne, au pays des sauvages Juracares [= large forests bordering the east of the Bolivian mountain range, in the country of the Yuracare Indians].” Restricted by S. Anderson and colleagues in 1982 to Yungas, between Rio Secire and Rio Isibara, 
<quantity box="[1223,1325,1512,1537]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.845" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" unit="m" value="1845.0">1845 m</quantity>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[745,848,1544,1577]" degrees="15" direction="south" minutes="45" orientation="latitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" precision="925" value="-15.75">15°45’S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[864,979,1544,1577]" degrees="65" direction="west" minutes="15" orientation="longitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" precision="925" value="-65.25">65°15’W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[995,1060,1544,1577]" country="Bolivia" name="Beni" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Beni</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1076,1170,1544,1577]" name="Bolivia" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="505" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[741,1333,1188,1616]" lastBlockId="21.[128,1337,1623,3474]" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">
Widely used name silvicolum has been changed as the substantival suffix cola is invariable, also subspecific names centralis and laephotis have been changed for gender agreement. 
<taxonomicName box="[822,1071,1663,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Thymelaeaceae" genus="Lophostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvicola">Lophostoma silvicola</taxonomicName>
was formerly in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[219,312,1702,1735]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tonatia</taxonomicName>
, but T. E. Lee and collaborators in 2002 showed that 
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1109,1702,1735]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tonatia</taxonomicName>
was paraphyletic and recommended to restrict it to 
<taxonomicName box="[596,703,1742,1775]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">1. bidens</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[772,930,1742,1775]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">1. saurophila</taxonomicName>
, while reclassifying remaining taxa to 
<taxonomicName box="[226,373,1781,1814]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Thymelaeaceae" genus="Lophostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="505" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Lophostoma</taxonomicName>
. Recently, the former subspecies occidentale from south-western 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1333,1781,1814]" name="Ecuador" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and north-western 
<collectingCountry box="[384,447,1820,1853]" name="Peru" pageId="21" pageNumber="505">Peru</collectingCountry>
was distinguished as a valid species. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
